@startuml container-two-build
'' ============================================================================
'' vinary-viewer â€” Container view: the two shadow-cljs builds + the preload seam
''
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because: we need a stereotyped trust boundary that
'' *encloses* the Chromium renderer, distinct artifact rectangles with per-build
'' fill colours, and a single amber IPC seam that physically sits between the two
'' processes. PlantUML rectangles + `together` grouping + the shared `_vv-theme`
'' palette express this; Mermaid's subgraphs cannot colour-code by concept nor
'' draw the contextBridge as a first-class boundary object.
'' ============================================================================
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title vinary-viewer â€” Containers (one source tree â†’ two builds, joined by the IPC seam)

skinparam rectangle {
  BorderThickness 1.6
  FontColor #1A1A1A
}

rectangle "shadow-cljs\n(`shadow-cljs.edn` â†’ 2 builds)" as Build REFRAME_TINT

package "Electron runtime" {

  rectangle "**MAIN process** (Node)\n`:main` build â†’ `:node-script`\n`dist/main/main.js`\nentry `vinary.main.core/main`" as Main MAIN_FILL {
    rectangle "main.core\nwindow + lifecycle" as MCore MAIN_TINT
    rectangle "main.service\nfs read Â· chokidar watch Â· git" as MSvc MAIN_TINT
  }

  rectangle "preload (IPC seam)\n`resources/preload.js`\ncontextBridge â†’ `window.vv`" as Preload IPC_TINT

  rectangle "trust boundary\n(contextIsolation = true,\nnodeIntegration = false)" as Boundary #line.dashed;line:B1951D {
    rectangle "**RENDERER process** (Chromium)\n`:renderer` build â†’ `:browser`\n`resources/public/js/main.js`\ninit `vinary.renderer.core/init`" as Rend RENDERER_FILL {
      rectangle "re-frame loop\n(events Â· subs Â· fx)" as RFrame REFRAME_TINT
      rectangle "DataScript conn\n(documents / tabs SSOT)" as DS DATASCRIPT_TINT
      rectangle "reagent UI (React 19)\n+ unified markdown" as UI RENDERER_TINT
    }
  }
}

Build --> Main          : compiles\n`:node-script`
Build --> Rend          : compiles\n`:browser`\n(fs/path/url âź¶ false)

MCore --> Preload       : `webPreferences.preload`
MSvc  ..> Preload       : `webContents.send`\n`vv:content` Â· `vv:error` Â· `vv:tree`
Preload ..> RFrame      : `window.vv.onContent/onError/onTree`\nâź¶ `rf/dispatch`
RFrame --> Preload      : `window.vv.open/close`
Preload ..> MSvc        : `ipcRenderer.send`\n`vv:open` Â· `vv:close`

RFrame --> DS  : `:ds/transact`
DS ..> RFrame  : `d/listen!` âź¶ `[:ds/changed]`\n(bumps `:ds/rev`)
RFrame --> UI  : subscriptions
MSvc --> MSvc  : reads filesystem\n(out of band)

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  |<#3A5BA0>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| MAIN / Node IO |
  |<#2D9574>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| Renderer / Chromium UI |
  |<#B1951D>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| IPC seam (preload / contextBridge) |
  |<#A45BAD>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| DataScript single-source-of-truth |
  |<#4F97D7>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| re-frame machinery / shadow-cljs |
  Dashed border = trust boundary Â· Amber arrow = IPC message
endlegend
@enduml
